{{Quote|We modified their genetic structure to make them less independent than the original host.''"<br />"''And who was the original host?''"<br />"''A bounty hunter called Jango Fett.|Lama Su and Obi-Wan Kenobi|<ref name="Episode II" />}}
A '''clone template''', also referred to as a '''donor''', an '''original host''', or the '''Prime Clone''', was the [[DNA|genetic]] source upon which a [[Cloning|clone]] was created. During the [[Republic Era|late era]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], the [[human]] [[bounty hunter]] [[Jango Fett]] became the template of an [[army]] of [[clone trooper]]s secretly built on the [[planet]] [[Kamino]].

[[Darth Sidious]], the [[Dark Lord of the Sith]] and [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] of the [[Galactic Empire]], engineered a clone of himself to serve as a vessel for his essence, thereby allowing him to resurrect himself after his first [[death]]. Sidious was also the template of his [[Dathan|cloned son]], a failed [[Strand-Cast|strandcast]] who was [[Bioengineering|engineered]] by the [[Sith Eternal]] [[Religion|cult]] on [[Exegol]].

==Overview==
{{Quote|The sample doesn't match anything found in the Jango Fett genotype. Furthermore, it is not even completely organic. It is foreign to the body. Someone implanted it there.|AZI-345211896246498721347|<ref name="Fugitive">{{TCW|Fugitive}}</ref>}}
[[Cloning]] was the scientific process of using a [[Species|living organism's]] [[DNA|genetic code]] as a template in order to create one or more clones of the original source.<ref name="TSWB">''[[The Star Wars Book]]''</ref> Without alterations to the template, the clone would be an exact duplicate of its progenitor. By manipulating the genetic structure of the template, a clone's genotype could be modified for various purposes such as growth acceleration and greater docility.<ref name="Episode II" />

[[File:CloneDNAroom-ARCT.png|thumb|left|250px|Millions of clones could be grown from a single genetic sample.]]

===Flaws===
A single genetic sample taken from an original organism was sufficient to grow millions of clones. Host samples degraded over [[time]], however, making the donor essential for replacement samples.<ref name="TSWB" /> The cloning process could be sustained without the original host, but only by rationing the last viable samples of DNA.<ref name="Clone Cadets">{{TCW|Clone Cadets}}</ref> Eventually a new template would have to be selected in order to grow more clones.<ref name="TSWB" />

The cloning of a [[human]] template was an imperfect science despite the [[Kaminoan]]s' efforts to perfect their craft as cloners. It was rare, but possible to find genetic and physical defects in their specimens, resulting in either desirable or undesirable clone aberrations.<ref name="TSWB" /> 

Furthermore, cloning a [[Force-sensitive]] template using Kaminoan methods did not guarantee that the clone would express its source's connection to [[the Force]]. Though the [[Galactic Empire]]'s [[Project Necromancer]] was initiated to correct this flaw in the Kaminoan cloning process, even by [[35 ABY]] and the [[Battle of Exegol]] and subsequent halt of the [[Imperial cloning program]], the process was never quite perfected, or at least, not by the Galactic Empire, and, while it was possible for its scientists to deliberately create Force-sensitive clones, in most cases, the clones would either end up successfully expressing Force-sensitivity, but not be stable, or, in a minority of cases, end up being perfectly stable but still not be guaranteed to express their donor's Force-sensitivity despite inheriting all of their DNA. [[Darth Sidious]] retained the use of his [[Force power]]s despite being confined to a genetically exact yet imperfectly grown and constructed cloned body of himself, while his [[Dathan|cloned son]], a not-quite-identical strandcast, was a healthy but seemingly powerless specimen. Nevertheless, even for cases when such a strandcast did not outwardly display inherited power, they retained the potential in a dormant state. Thus,  it was possible for the genetic donor's dormant Force-sensitivity to be expressed by the next generation in their [[Palpatine family|bloodline]], as was the case with [[Rey Skywalker|Rey]], Sidious' biological granddaughter.<ref name="TROS EE" />

==History==
===A clone army===
{{Quote|I do believe that this army will be our finest creation yet. Not a single clone unit has fallen below combat parameters. You must be very proud.''"<br />"''What do I have to be proud of? Livestock bred as cannon fodder? Like you said, they're ''your'' creations.|Taun We and Jango Fett|<ref name="AoR-Jango Fett">[[Age of Republic - Jango Fett 1|''Age of Republic - Jango Fett'' 1]]</ref>}}
[[File:JangoFettMeetsWithDooku-AORJangoFett1.png|thumb|right|250px|The Sith chose a bounty hunter, Jango Fett, to be the template of a clone army.]]
During the final [[Standard year|years]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], the [[Sith Lord]] [[Dooku|Darth Tyranus]] recruited [[Jango Fett]]&mdash;a human [[bounty hunter]]&mdash;as the genetic template of a secret [[army]] of [[clone trooper]]s. Fett would come to live on the [[planet]] [[Kamino]] where the Kaminoans, a [[species]] of skilled cloners, extracted samples of his DNA in order to create the first generation of clone [[soldier]]s for the Republic. In addition to the [[mercenary]]'s [[Galactic Credit Standard|financial]] compensation, Fett requested the creation of an unaltered clone of himself. The result was [[Boba Fett]],<ref name="Episode II" /> a clone whom Jango regarded as a son.<ref name="R2 Come Home">{{TCW|R2 Come Home}}</ref>

The [[Ruling Council (Kamino)|Kaminoan government's]] [[scientist]]s modified Jango Fett's genotype for the purpose of producing loyal clones at an accelerated rate. With the exception of Boba, who was grown through pure genetic replication, the rest of Jango's clones were designed to age at twice the speed of natural-born humans.<ref name="Episode II" /> To ensure loyalty and obedience in the clones, the Kaminoans installed an [[Behavioral modification biochip|inhibitor chip]] within the [[brain]] of every Fett clone.<ref name="Clone troopers">{{Databank|clone-troopers|Clone Troopers}}</ref> The chip's official purpose was to diminish the aggressive traits of the clone template so that the clones would be more compliant with orders.<ref name="Fugitive" /> Although the Kaminoans believed that the chip was actually meant to serve as a contingency against rogue [[Jedi]],<ref name="Conspiracy">{{TCW|Conspiracy}}</ref> the true nature of its design would compel the clones to execute [[Order 66]]&mdash;a secret protocol conceived by the [[Sith]] in their plot to destroy the [[Jedi Order]].<ref name="Orders">{{TCW|Orders (episode)}}</ref>

[[File:Clonestraining.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Fett's genetic samples were used to create millions of clone troopers for the Galactic Republic.]]
In spite of [[Taun We]]'s confidence in the clone [[army]]'s training, Fett was indifferent to them, referring to his cloned progeny as "livestock" bred to fight and die as "[[cannon]] fodder." He dismissed the Kaminoan [[aide]]'s assumption that he would be proud of his clones, and reminded Taun We that they were the Kaminoans' creations.<ref name="AoR-Jango Fett" />

During the [[Separatist Crisis]], [[Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] discovered the clone army on Kamino while investigating an [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala|assassination plot]] against [[Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala]]. [[Prime Minister]] [[Lama Su]] and Taun We took him on an inspection tour of the cloning facility in [[Tipoca City]], believing he had been dispatched at the behest of the [[Jedi High Council]] and the [[Galactic Senate]]. During the tour, Kenobi learned the identity of clone army's template, Jango Fett, who was also the would-be [[assassin]] who tried to kill Amidala. Kenobi reported his findings to his superiors, [[Grand Master]] [[Yoda]] and [[Jedi Master]] [[Mace Windu]], who ordered him to bring the hunter to the [[Imperial Palace|Jedi Grand Temple]] on [[Coruscant]] for interrogation.<ref name="Episode II" />

===Clone Wars===
{{Quote|However, I have noticed this unit of clones have been&hellip;''"<br />"''Deficient? My only thought is for you to search the galaxy and find a suitable donor for your future clones.|Shaak Ti and Lama Su|<ref name="Clone Cadets" />}}
Following the [[death]] of Jango Fett in the [[First Battle of Geonosis]]<ref name="Episode II" /> in [[22 BBY]],<ref name="GA">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref> the Kaminoans were forced to conserve their remaining samples of the Fett genome in order to grow more clones for the newly-formed [[Grand Army of the Republic]]. As a result, the new clones were less efficient according to Lama Su, who recommended to Jedi Master [[Shaak Ti]] that the Order should procure another template due to their waning supply of Fett DNA.<ref name="Clone Cadets" /> As the [[Clone Wars]] continued to spread across [[the galaxy]], the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]] [[Battle of Kamino|invaded]] Kamino<ref name="ARC Troopers">{{TCW|ARC Troopers (episode)}}</ref> with the aim of halting the world's cloning production.<ref name="TSWB" /> The [[Republic Military]] successfully defended Tipoca [[City]] from the [[Separatist Droid Army]] while [[Jedi General]] [[Anakin Skywalker]] prevented [[Asajj Ventress]] from stealing the last supply of Fett's genetic samples.<ref name="ARC Troopers" />

[[File:X-Alpha_heavy_cargo_sled.png|thumb|right|250px|The Zillo Beast's corpse was preserved for cloning purposes.]]
Shortly after the [[Battle of Malastare|discovery]] of the [[Zillo Beast]] on [[Malastare]], the [[Republic Military]] transferred the creature to the Republic [[capital]] for scientific study. In the aftermath of the beast's [[Zillo Beast incident|escape]] and subsequent death, [[Supreme Chancellor]] Sheev Palpatine ordered [[Doctor]] [[Sionver Boll]] to utilize its corpse as a clone template.<ref name="The Zillo Beast">{{TCW|The Zillo Beast}}</ref> The Empire's [[Advanced Science Division]] later succeeded in utilizing this prime clone to create a line of zillo beast clones which were kept in the [[Tantiss Base]] on [[Wayland]].<ref name="Metamorphosis">{{TBB|Metamorphosis (episode)}}</ref>

A [[Battle of Ringo Vinda|premature execution of Order 66]] led [[Fives|CT-5555]] "Fives," an [[Advanced Recon Commando]] with the [[501st Legion]], to [[Escape from Tipoca City|investigate]] the cause of Jedi [[General]] [[Tiplar]]'s death at the hands of [[Tup|CT-5385]] "Tup." Aided by the [[medical droid]] [[AZI-345211896246498721347]], Fives learned that the "tumor" in Tup's brain was not part of the original Jango Fett genome; it was in fact an artificial construct that had been implanted in every clone during the initial phase of their development. To protect the secrecy of Order 66, [[Doctor]] [[Nala Se]] claimed that the devices were inhibitor chips designed to guarantee the troopers' docility by suppressing their inherent aggression as clones of Fett.<ref name="Fugitive" />

===Legacy===
{{Quote|This armor belonged to my father.''"<br />"''Don't you mean your donor?''"<br />"''Careful, princess.''"<br />"''You are a clone. I've heard your voice thousands of times.|Boba Fett and Bo-Katan Kryze|<ref name="Chapter 16">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 16: The Rescue}}</ref>}}
[[File:FettLives-TMCh9.png|thumb|left|250px|Boba Fett considered Jango his father, but others recognized him as the clone of a man long since dead.]]
Jango Fett's clones were decommissioned shortly after the [[Proclamation of the New Order|proclamation]] of the [[Galactic Empire]], replaced as [[stormtrooper]]s by [[Reproduction|natural-born]] recruits during the early [[Imperial Era]].<ref name="Stormtroopers">{{Databank|stormtroopers|Stormtroopers}}</ref> After the [[New Republic]] came to [[New Republic Era|power]], the [[Mandalorian]] [[Din Djarin]]&mdash;working with Boba Fett&mdash;sought the help of [[Bo-Katan Kryze]] in his [[Second rescue of Grogu|quest to rescue]] the [[foundling]] [[Din Grogu|Grogu]]. Kryze denounced Fett, declaring that he was not a Mandalorian but a clone who disgraced the [[Mandalorian armor]] he wore. Fett told her that [[Boba Fett's armor|his armor]] once belonged to his father, Jango, whom Kryze referred to as Boba's donor. She recognized Boba's voice as that of the late Jango, having heard it thousands of times through the clone troopers who were modeled on the same genetic template.<ref name="Chapter 16" />

[[File:InsiderIntel-Palpatine.png|thumb|right|250px|Darth Sidious survived death by transferring his soul to a clone of his original body.]]
[[Darth]] Sidious&mdash;[[Dark Lord of the Sith]] and [[Galactic Emperor]]&mdash;was the template for multiple [[Bioengineering|genetically engineered]] clones created on [[Exegol]] by the [[Sith Eternal]].<ref name="TROS EE" /> After Sidious' death in the [[Battle of Endor]], his [[Transference|consciousness was thrust]] into cloned body of himself.<ref name="TSWB" /> His new body was flawed, however, as was the transference, leaving Sidious trapped in a weak and decaying vessel. The [[Sith cultist]]s who served him sought to create a more stable host for their [[Sith Master|master's]] essence, resulting in various failed [[Strand-Cast|strandcasts]]. The [[Padawan|Jedi apprentice]] Rey was a byproduct of the Sith Eternal's experiments, being the natural-born daughter of Sidious' cloned son. Though she inherited her grandfather's connection to the Force, Rey rejected the [[Dark side of the Force|dark side]] and was instrumental in the destruction of Sidious' cloned vessel during the [[Battle of Exegol]].<ref name="TROS EE" />

